<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF2636632FE892CFECEF370" blockId="5.[174,1233,1445,1859]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1225,910,1100]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
Diagnosis. 
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF26365339D892CFC95F1BC" bold="true" box="[384,472,1638,1664]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Female</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF263653068892CF977F1BD" authority="(Malm, 1863)" baseAuthorityName="Malm" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[629,1082,1638,1665]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrogona">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF263653068892CFEDDF1BC" box="[629,912,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Orthonevra erythrogona</emphasis>
(Malm, 1863)
</taxonomicName>
by legs with tibiae pale at least for basal 1/3 (almost half in the specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="49E9F810FFF26365318389CCF962F19D" box="[926,1071,1670,1697]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Kyiv Region</collectingRegion>
, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF26365366789CCF98FF19D" box="[1146,1218,1670,1697]" captionStart="Figs 22–25" captionStartId="6.[166,205,819,841]" captionTargetBox="[251,1147,174,797]" captionTargetId="figure-438@6.[250,1147,174,798]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 22–25. Female of Orthonevra geniculata: 22 — habitus, dorsal view; 23 — lateral view; 24 — head, frontal view; 25 — right wing (arrow shows the dark maculae on the basis of stigma and around the crossvein r-m)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454618/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">FIg. 23</figureCitation>
), and the basoflagellomere about 3 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF26365314C89EDFED0F1FE" box="[849,925,1703,1730]" captionStart="Figs 22–25" captionStartId="6.[166,205,819,841]" captionTargetBox="[251,1147,174,797]" captionTargetId="figure-438@6.[250,1147,174,798]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 22–25. Female of Orthonevra geniculata: 22 — habitus, dorsal view; 23 — lateral view; 24 — head, frontal view; 25 — right wing (arrow shows the dark maculae on the basis of stigma and around the crossvein r-m)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454618/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">FIg. 24</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF2636531C989EDF9CFF1FD" baseAuthorityName="Malm" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[980,1154,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrogona">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF2636531C989EDF9CFF1FD" box="[980,1154,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">O. erythrogona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tibiae black with only knees pale, and the basoflagellomere twice as long as wide). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF2636532B389ADFCDFF03D" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[174,402,1767,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF2636532B389ADFCDFF03D" box="[174,402,1767,1793]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Orthonevra elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann in Meigen, 1822) 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF26365310589A2FEFBF03D" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[792,950,1767,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculata">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF26365310589A2FEFBF03D" box="[792,950,1767,1794]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">O. geniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by eyes without dark stripe, and the basoflagellomere about 3 times longer than wide (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF2636536058842F9DDF01E" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1048,1168,1800,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF2636536058842F9DDF01E" box="[1048,1168,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">O. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, eyes with dark stripe, and the basoflagellomere about 4 times longer than wide). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF1636632BB8CC5FF43F495" authority="Lundbeck, 1916" authorityName="Lundbeck" authorityYear="1916" box="[166,526,910,937]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF1636632BB8CC5FC04F494" box="[166,329,910,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">O. intermedia</emphasis>
Lundbeck, 1916
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF1636630568CC5F968F495" authority="Thompson &amp; Torp, 1982" authorityName="Thompson &amp; Torp" authorityYear="1982" box="[587,1061,910,937]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stackelbergi">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF1636630568CC5FFB8F494" box="[587,757,910,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">O. stackelbergi</emphasis>
Thompson &amp; Torp, 1982
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF1636636308CC5F984F494" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1069,1225,910,937]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculata">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF1636636308CC5F984F494" box="[1069,1225,910,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">O. geniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the crossvein r-m brown infuscate and two-colored pterostigma (yellowish with dark part at base) (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF1636633948C85FC95F4D6" box="[393,472,975,1002]" captionStart="Figs 22–25" captionStartId="6.[166,205,819,841]" captionTargetBox="[251,1147,174,797]" captionTargetId="figure-438@6.[250,1147,174,798]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 22–25. Female of Orthonevra geniculata: 22 — habitus, dorsal view; 23 — lateral view; 24 — head, frontal view; 25 — right wing (arrow shows the dark maculae on the basis of stigma and around the crossvein r-m)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454618/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">FIg. 25</figureCitation>
), face on the level of the antennal sockets about 1.5–2 times as wide as width of an eye (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF1636633CE8CBAFF6FF337" box="[467,546,1008,1035]" captionStart="Figs 22–25" captionStartId="6.[166,205,819,841]" captionTargetBox="[251,1147,174,797]" captionTargetId="figure-438@6.[250,1147,174,798]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 22–25. Female of Orthonevra geniculata: 22 — habitus, dorsal view; 23 — lateral view; 24 — head, frontal view; 25 — right wing (arrow shows the dark maculae on the basis of stigma and around the crossvein r-m)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454618/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">FIg. 24</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF1636630428CBAFE47F336" authorityName="Thompson &amp; Torp" authorityYear="1982" box="[607,778,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stackelbergi">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF1636630428CBAFE47F336" box="[607,778,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">O. stackelbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF1636631548CBAFEABF336" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[841,998,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculata">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF1636631548CBAFEABF336" box="[841,998,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">O. geniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the crossvein r-m clear, pterostigma unicolorous, the width of the face on the level of the antennal sockets less than the width of an eye) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF1636633C78B7BFFE6F370" author="Stackelberg, A. A." box="[474,683,1073,1100]" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" pagination="342 - 357" refId="ref5793" refString="Stackelberg, A. A. 1953. Palaearctic species of the genus Orthoneura Macq. (Diptera, Syrphidae). Entomological Review, 33, 342 - 357." type="journal article" year="1953">Stackelberg, 1953</bibRefCitation>
; 
<collectingRegion id="49E9F810FFF1636630AB8B7BFFA5F370" box="[694,744,1073,1100]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">Van</collectingRegion>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF1636630F38B7BFE3AF370" author="Veen, M. P. &amp; Van" box="[750,887,1073,1100]" pageId="6" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 248" refId="ref6016" refString="Veen, M. P., Van. 2010. Hoverflies of Northwest Europe. Identification keys to the Syrphidae. Second edition. KNNV Publishing, Utrecht, 1 - 248." type="book chapter" year="2010">
<collectingRegion id="49E9F810FFF1636630F38B7BFE63F370" box="[750,814,1073,1100]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="6" pageNumber="131">Veen</collectingRegion>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
